Boil a #pot{} of 700ml (exactly) of water with @salt{1/2%tsp}, and pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{2}. Chop the @aubergine{1} lengthways into about 8 strips then chop into 3cm chunks. Remove the ends of the @green beans{1/2} and chop into thirds.

Put the @basmati rice{1} into the pot of boiling water. Cover with a tight #lid{} and place on the lowest heat for ~{10%minutes}. Take the pot off the heat to rest for ~{10%minutes}.

> Tip: Do not lift the lid from the pot at all during cooking and resting.

Coat the aubergine evenly in @olive oil{3%tbsp}. Sprinkle over @salt{1/2%tsp} and a generous amount of @black pepper{}. Tip onto a #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf of the oven until slightly crispy (~{20%minutes}).

Heat a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Without adding oil, put your @cashew nuts{2} in the pan. Leave them for around ~{5%minutes}, shaking the pan constantly, to brown, then remove to one side.

> Tip: Watch your nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to the empty non-stick frying pan together with the @massaman curry paste{1}. Stir the paste for ~{1%minute} and then add the @coconut milk{200} and chestnut mushrooms. Once the coconut milk comes to the boil add the green beans and the @peanut butter{1.5} and turn the heat to low. Gently simmer for ~{10%minutes}.

Add the roasted aubergine into the curry mixture.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and add it to the pan with the massaman mixture in it. Gently fold the rice and three-quarters of the coriander into the sauce. Squeeze over the juice of the @lime{1/2}. Serve into #bowls{} and garnish with the remaining coriander and cashews.